## <a id='filestore'></a>Step 13: Configure File Storage ##

When configuring file storage for the Cloud Controller in Elastic Runtime, you can select:

* Internal WebDAV filestore (appropriate for small, non-production deployments)
* External S3 or Ceph-compatible filestore
* External Google Cloud Storage  
* External Azure Cloud Storage

Pivotal recommends using external highly resilient and redundant filestores for your Elastic Runtime file storage. This approach minimizes system downtime. 

For PCF deployments on GCP, the recommended selection is Google Cloud Storage.

For more factors to consider when selecting file storage, see <a href="../opsguide/storage_considerations.html">Considerations for Selecting File Storage in Pivotal Cloud Foundry</a>. 

1. In the Elastic Runtime tile, select **File Storage**.

### <a id='internal_filestore'></a> Internal Filestore

